      <h1 class=3D"entry-title">Effective Field Goal Percentage (eFG%)</h1>
   =20
  </header>     =20


<div class=3D"entry-content content">


  <hr class=3D"x-hr">
<nav aria-label=3D"breadcrumbs" class=3D"rank-math-breadcrumb"><p><a href=
=3D"https://www.nbastuffer.com/">Home</a><span class=3D"separator"> =C2=BB =
</span><a href=3D"https://www.nbastuffer.com/analytics101/">Analytics 101</=
a><span class=3D"separator"> =C2=BB </span><span class=3D"last">Effective F=
ield Goal Percentage (eFG%)</span></p></nav>
<b>Effective Field Goal Percentage</b>, aka eFG%, is a player or team evalu=
ation metric that measures the effectiveness of 2-point shots and 3-point s=
hots.<p></p>
<div id=3D"" class=3D"x-alert x-alert-info x-alert-block" style=3D""><h6 cl=
ass=3D"h-alert">Effective Field Goal Percentage (eFG%) Formula</h6>
<b>Effective Field Goal Percentage Formula</b>=3DeFG%=3D{(All Field Goals M=
ade) + 0.5*(3P Field Goals Made)}/(All Field Goal Attempts)<br>
<br>
<img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"x-img x-img-rounded=
" style=3D"max-width: 50%;" src=3D"https://cdn.nbastuffer.com/wp-content/up=
loads/2025/02/efg.png" alt=3D"Effective Field Goal Percentage Formula">
</div>
<p>In terms of FG% and eFG%, two players can be compared. Two players with =
the same FG% should not be evaluated as they have the same performance. Whe=
n you bring eFG% on the table, you=E2=80=99ll find out that the player who =
had more three-point shots would have a better eFG%. Head over to <a href=
=3D"https://www.nbastuffer.com/nba-stats/player/">player stats</a> tables t=
o sort or filter players by eFG% values. </p>
<p class=3D"wpg-back-link"><a href=3D"https://www.nbastuffer.com/analytics-=
101/">Back to Analytics101</a></p><p> =20

</p></div>

